All Classes and Interfaces

Classes
Class
Description
CashierPage
The CashierPage class represents the GUI for the cashier system.
Db
This class handles database connectivity and queries using PostgreSQL.
EmployeePanel
The EmployeePanel class provides a graphical interface for managing employees.
FrameStyle
The FrameStyle class provides utility methods for styling JFrame windows.
ItemList
The ItemList class represents a JFrame window that displays a list of items belonging to a specific product type.
JobSelectionPage
The JobSelectionPage class represents a JFrame window that allows employees to select their role upon logging in.
LoginScreen
The LoginScreen class represents a JFrame window for user authentication.
Main
The Main class serves as the entry point for the application.
ManagerPage
This class handles the Manager page on the gui.
PasswordHash
The PasswordHash class provides a utility method to hash passwords using the SHA-256 algorithm.
ProductEntry
The ProductEntry class represents a product with an ID, name, and price.
ProductUsePanel
Panel to display the use of products.
SalesReport
Panel to report sales of each product over a time interval.
Utils
The Utils class provides utility methods for string formatting.
XReportPanel
This class represents a panel for displaying an X-Report, which shows sales data per hour for a selected date.
ZReportPanel
The ZReportPanel class represents a panel that generates and displays the Z-Report.
